<H2>Commit Window</H2>
<P>The Commit Window shows the progress of an installation, upgrade or removal of a
package and it's dependencies.</P>
<P>It displays a message of what stage in the process it is in and a progress bar to show
how far through the operation it is.</P>
<P>If the operation completes successfully. Click on the button to dismiss it.</P>
<p>If the one or more upgrades to already installed packages are detected in the new
lists the Upgrade All button will be enabled that leads to the
<a href="upgradeall.htm">Upgrade All Window</a> that allows all the upgrades to be
applied at once.</p>
<P>If the operation fails an error window will be shown with the cause of the failure.</P>
<P>If the failure is caused because there are already files in the location it would like
to install files in one of the installed packages the <A HREF="conflictman.htm">Conflict Manager Window</A>
showing information on the conflicting files will be shown instead.</P>
</BODY>
